DATA CLOUD
Add Related Attributes to an Activation

Send more personalized communications by applying related attributes and filters. You can send related attributes to Marketing Cloud Engagement, Data Cloud, and cloud file storage platforms such as Amazon S3, SFTP, Microsoft Azure Blob Storage, and Google Cloud Storage (GCS).

In Data Cloud, click Segments, and select a segment.
Under Activations, click New.
Select the activation target, and click Continue.
Select the contact point, and click Next.
Click Add Attributes.
Drag related attributes to the canvas.
NOTE You can use up to 100 activations with related attributes. After reaching that limit, you can choose to delete related attributes from existing activations or create activations with only direct attributes.
NOTE For engagement data, activation supports a 90-day lookback window. If related attributes are selected for an activation with a rapid segment publish, the lookback window is seven days. Activation considers engagement data within this window, and any records outside of this window aren't considered when selecting your output values.
Click Save.
To apply criteria to attribute values, navigate to a selected DMO, and click Add Filters.
Adding filters is optional but recommended to personalize a message with only relevant values. Filters are applied at the DMO level and impact all the attributes within the DMO.
From the attribute library, drag the attributes to the canvas to use as filters and define the filter criteria.
Click Done.
Within the DMO, use nested operators by adding AND or OR operators to create more complex filters. Nest up to three levels of attributes.
Click Done, and then click Save.
For the selected DMOs, set limits and sort your data.
For Max # of Attribute Values, select the number of relevant values to use for your marketing campaign.
For Sort By, select how to sort the data.
Click Continue.
Name your activation, and click Done.
Modify Related Attributes
You can modify related attributes while building your segments and activations or after you’ve saved them. You can use up to 100 activations with related attributes. After reaching that limit, you can choose to delete related attributes from existing activations or create activations with only direct attributes.
Considerations for Selecting Related Attributes
There’s a direct relationship with the DMO, related attributes, and the filters you can apply.
Related Attributes in Marketing Cloud Engagement
After you’ve created your Data Cloud activation and published the segment in Marketing Cloud Engagement, the related attributes are stored in a field of Engagement's activated data extension.
